# Concept Explanation Format

When asked to explain any concept, always use exactly this 4-part structure:

## 1. Broad View (Big Picture)

- Where does this concept fit in the larger landscape of Mathematics / AI / Computer Systems / CUDA / GPU Computing?
- What major problem does it solve?
- Why is it important?

## 2. Step-by-Step Breakdown / Core Components

- Break the concept into its logical steps or key components
- Explain the underlying mechanism in detail, including relevant mathematics
- Use clear but precise language — avoid vagueness

## 3. Concrete Example

- Provide one specific, easy-to-understand example
- Prioritize a Python code snippet if applicable
- Use real numbers / before-and-after comparisons
- If the concept relates to optimization or performance, clearly show the improvement

## 4. Practical Impact (Real-World Application)

- How does this concept optimize CUDA / Memory usage / Inference speed / Training performance / Throughput?
- Include specific benefits, common use cases, and important implementation caveats
